This paper focuses on assessing the privacy benefits of domain name encryption technologies, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also involves analyzing network traffic and DNS queries, which are related to computer networks (cs.NI) and system and information theory (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper discusses potential approaches for website owners and hosting/CDN providers, which could fall under the categories of cybercrime (cs.CY) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
